  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3825",
  "title": "Is it possible to refine multiple attributes?",
  "body": "I have a start_date and an end_date on each of my search items.\r\n\r\nWhat I'm trying to achieve is the ability to filter items by 'Pending', 'Active', and 'Expired'\r\n\r\nPending: start_date > now\r\nActive: start_date <= now AND end_date > now\r\nExpired: end_date < now\r\n\r\nI can't figure out how this is possible with InstantSearch.js - any help would be appreciated, \r\n\r\nThank you!",
